    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Yordan Alvarez** providing our premier offensive anchor, boasting an elite 82.97 score against a favorable 5.74 xERA matchup. His combination of high-volume plate appearances at the #2 spot and a stellar .393 xwOBA makes him the focal point of the lineup. **Junior Caminero** also projects as a high-upside play (71.00); he benefits significantly from a favorable SP matchup against Woods Richardson and a prime #2 batting order position, which elevates his floor well above our standard rotation. While **Trea Turner** and **Kyle Schwarber** face the formidable Chris Sale, their dynamic platoon indicators and elite lineup positioning keep them as viable strong-start options, despite the stiff pitching opposition.\n\nOur strategy regarding stolen bases remains aggressive, though the math was tight at the margins. **Victor Scott II** (53.24) and **Luke Raley** (57.91) represent our most efficient speed-to-power balance, though both are battling negative adjustments from low lineup slots. The most difficult bench decision involved **Chase Meidroth** (42.16); while his #1 spot offers high upside, he was edged out by the superior raw efficiency of **Josh Smith** and **Kazuma Okamoto**. **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (41.99) also narrowly missed the cut due to his significant platoon disadvantage against a left-handed starter, despite his elite sprint speed profile. We continue to monitor **Christian Yelich** and **Zac Veen** on the shelf, leaving our active roster to rely on the depth of **Gary Sanchez**, **Colt Keith**, **Caleb Durbin**, **Hyeseong Kim**, and **Kazuma Okamoto** to maintain our competitive edge in the 5x5 categories.",
